Microwave Caramel  (makes enough to coat 8 ramekins)

1/2 cup granulated sugar
1/4 cup light corn syrup
5 drops fresh lemon juice

1.  Place all ingredients in a 2 or 4 cup glass measuring cup.  Stir 
until sugar is moistened.

2.  Cook in microwave until bubbles start piling up on top of each other 
and mixture turns amber in color, approximately 3 minutes.

3.  Carefully remove and divide between ramekins.  Use caution sugar 
mixture is extremely hot.  Let cool until hard.

